This paper proposes a linear K-hyperplane classifier for AUC maximization, which is a machine learning algorithm. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with classification performance on imbalanced data, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method is evaluated on several benchmark datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses unsupervised learning and local coding algorithm, which are techniques used in data mining (cs.DM).
